    <h2>Final Verdict</h2>

    <div class="verdict">
      <p>Google Drive offers the best value with generous free storage and collaboration.</p>
      <p>Dropbox offers the best file sync and sharing experience.</p>
      <p>OneDrive offers the best Office integration for Microsoft 365 users. Both Google Drive and Dropbox are excellent choices in the productivity category. Your final decision should be based on your specific requirements, budget, and preferred workflow. We recommend testing both platforms with their free tiers before committing to a paid plan.</p>
